Filtering Records Extracted from a Salesforce Object

A filter consists of one or more filter conditions, where each filter condition compares a field value to a value. You can add multiple filter conditions using logical operators AND, OR, and NOT.

The sfdcDigest Transformation transformation extracts all records for which the filter is true.

For each instance of sfdcDigest, you can use one of the following types of filters: Structured filter or Advanced filter.

NOTE Filtering records extracted from Salesforce Big Objects is supported only on primary key fields in the sfdcDigest Transformation transformation.
